  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <p>Drupal's Taxonomy system has offered the ability to store <em>synonyms</em> for almost a decade. When the term 'Chicago' is defined as a category, for example, Drupal allows you to add 'Windy City' as a potential alternative. What Drupal <em>doesn't</em> do, however, is <em>use</em> that synonym anywhere. That's where the <a href="http://drupal.org/project/synonyms">Synonyms</a> module comes in.</p>
